Hersteller Beschreibung / Sales Text: Ultra-light, state-of-the-art foam supplies game-changing rebound and softness in the new ECCO M GOLF LT1. This innovative men’s hybrid is created using new ECCO LYTR, an advanced bounce and rebound foam that is embedded in the sole via signature FLUIDFORM™ technology. The foam is seamlessly combined in the midsole with soft PU, which provides contoured comfort, stability and a longlasting integral bond to the leather upper. For low-to-the-ground stability, the ECCO M GOLF LT1 has a visible shank and the new E-DTS™ NET outsole is a fresh twist on the ECCO DYNAMIC TRACTION SYSTEM™ and offers multi-directional traction and durability. While the waterproof membrane keeps the foot dry, the clean, sneaker-style aesthetic and ECCO leather add to the premium look and feel. The BOA® Fit System delivers a micro-adjustable precision fit engineered to perform in any conditions. - Ultra-light rebound and softness with new ECCO LYTR, an advanced foam that is embedded in the sole via FLUIDFORM™ technology - Foam is seamlessly combined in the midsole with soft PU for contoured comfort, stability and an integral bond to the upper -  - New E-DTS™ NET outsole is a fresh take on the E-DTS® design that offers multi-directional traction and durability - Breathable, premium ECCO Performance Leather and a waterproof membrane

The BOA® Fit System delivers a micro-adjustable precision fit engineered to perform in any conditions. - Ultra-light rebound and softness with new ECCO LYTR, an advanced foam that is embedded in the sole via FLUIDFORM™ technology - Foam is seamlessly combined in the midsole with soft PU for contoured comfort, stability and an integral bond to the upper -  - New E-DTS™ NET outsole is a fresh take on the E-DTS® design that offers multi-directional traction and durability - Breathable, premium ECCO Performance Leather and a waterproof membrane

Beschreibung MyGolfOutlet:
P790 Limited Copper Edition Eisen von TaylorMade

  • Modernes klassisches Design: Feiern des 1980er TaylorMade-Logos mit einer alt-aussehenden Kupferoberfläche, die im Laufe der Zeit eine einzigartige Vintage-Optik erhält.
  • Optimierung der Masse: Fortschrittliche dick-dünn Rückwandkonstruktion mit KI-optimierter Massenverteilung für verbesserte Leistung und präzises Gewicht in jedem Eisen.
  • FLTD CG™ Technologie: Strategische Platzierung des Schwerpunkts, der in langen Eisen niedriger und in kurzen Eisen höher liegt, für bessere Starteigenschaften und Kontrolle.
  • Intelligenter Sweet Spot: Vergrößerter Sweet Spot und reaktionsfreudige Schlagfläche sorgen für konstante Ballgeschwindigkeiten und Genauigkeit bei mehr Schlägen.
